** About the Project **   
The Drupal 9 developer will be responsible for contributing to the
redevelopment of the web presence to ensure a fit-for-purpose, user-focused
and best practice solution. This role will focus on the planning, technical
design and development of the Drupal 9 website and will work collaboratively
with the ICT web technical team and website project team.  
  
** Duties for this role are **   

  * Work collaboratively with the website project team to develop the Drupal 9 website, ensuring the new website meets user needs, provides an optimal user experience, and meets technical standards. 
  * Provide expert technical advice to ensure the successful delivery of the website, and contribute to planning development sprints to ensure goals and deadlines are met, and milestones are delivered. 
  * Migrate, redevelop or reconfigure content types from the existing Drupal 7 websites. 
  * Develop scripts for content migration from Drupal 7 websites. 
  * Make sound technical recommendations and provide advice to the project team. 
  * Knowledge transfer to Web Team. 
** The Ideal Candidate Will Have **   

  * Minimum of 5 yearsâ€™ experience and advanced proficiency in Drupal website development, including strong experience in backend and front-end Drupal 9 site development and configuration, themes, views, content type definition, search configuration, taxonomy development, and testing. 
  * Proficiency in HTML, UX, PHP, MySQL, Linux, Apache and knowledge of relevant standards including Digital Service Standard and WCAG 2.1 AA compliance. Proficiency with CSS and pre-processors such as Sass or LESS. 
  * Advanced knowledge of JavaScript and frameworks such as jQuery. 
  * Experience in developing and supporting Drupal in an AWS environment. Experience in moving from Drupal 7 to Drupal 9. 
  * Experience with end-to-end product planning and execution and working on large website development projects including content migration. Excellent written, verbal and interpersonal communication skills. 

